The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to planar regions and points, and specifically focuses on preprocessing techniques to improve the efficiency of computing certain structures on these points. This suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data structures and algorithms, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses trade-offs between space and query time, which is a topic often studied in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the construction of convex hulls, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under cs.GR (Graphics) as well. Finally, the paper involves probabilistic analysis, which is a common technique in cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification).
